		"description": "<p>Also at 2nd level, you have learned how to transfer some of the unnatural prowess of your blood into your weapon strikes, enabling you to do additional damage. The type of damage that your Sanguine Transference deals is found under your archetype.</p>\n<p>Whenever you hit with a melee or ranged weapon attack, you may add 1d8 of the specific damage type to your roll. This damage increases to 2d8 at 6th level, 3d8 at 10th level, 4d8 at 15th level, and 5d8 at 18th level. You may use your Sanguine Transference a number of times equal to your proficiency bonus per long rest.</p>",
